Monaco — Holders Real Madrid will face Borussia Dortmund and Tottenham Hotspur in the Champions League group stage while Barcelona were drawn with Juventus on Thursday. Zinedine Zidane’s side are chasing a third successive European title as well as a fourth title in five seasons. The European champions will also take on Apoel of Cyprus in a testing Group H. World-record signing Neymar and Paris Saint-Germain were paired alongside Bayern Munich, with Scottish champions Celtic and Belgium’s Anderlecht completing the line-up in Group B. Chelsea will meet Atletico Madrid in Group C as well as Roma and Qarabag, the first side from Azerbaijan to reach this stage. Manchester United drew Benfica in Group A along with CSKA Moscow and Basel. Manchester City are in Group F alongside Ukrainian champions Shakhtar Donetsk, Napoli and Feyenoord while Liverpool will play Spartak Moscow, Sevilla and Maribor in Group E. Monaco face Porto, Besiktas and RB Leipzig in Group G. AFP